menu "GoPro Controller — SoftAP / Local network"

    config WIFI_AP_IP_ADDR
        string "SoftAP IPv4 address"
        default "10.71.79.1"
        help
            IPv4 address of the controller's SoftAP interface. This is also used
            as the gateway and as the DHCP-offered DNS server, and the DHCP lease
            pool is derived from its /24 subnet (.2 – .50). The netmask is fixed
            at 255.255.255.0.

            Clients reach the web UI at http://<this address>/ and at the
            friendly name below. If the string fails to parse, the firmware logs
            a warning and falls back to 10.71.79.1.

            Set the same value in both apps' sdkconfig.defaults (main + recovery)
            so a browser left on the domain resolves identically in either mode.

    config WIFI_LOCAL_DOMAIN
        string "Friendly local domain name"
        default "control.gp"
        help
            Hostname the SoftAP DNS responder (local_dns) resolves to the SoftAP
            address; every other name gets NXDOMAIN. Typing this in a browser on
            a connected client opens the web UI.

            Keep a real, non-searchable TLD suffix (the default ".gp" is a live
            TLD). A bare label with no dot (e.g. "controller") is treated as a
            search term by some browsers and will not resolve.

endmenu
